Row.aggChangesComment: A new UWWTP will be build to treat all the waste water issued from the municipalities of Wasserbillig, Mertert, Grevenmacher, Stadtbredimus, Lenningen and Wormeldange. The new capacity is 47000 p.e.
Row.aggRemarks: for all agglomerations the aggPeriodOver should be 31-12-1998. The agglomeration of Grevenmacher has several sub agglomerations (commune of Wasserbillig, Mertert, Grevenmacher, Stadtbredimus, Lenningen, Manternach and Wormeldange). All these small sub agglomerations have there own collecting system already in place. It is foreseen to connect all these sub agglomerations via a new sewer pipe to a new UWWTP to be build in the agglomeration of Grevenmacher.

Row.aggChangesComment: Since April 2010 the new UWWTP is operational and is able to treat 99% of the agglomeration of Remich. The UWWTP is located in Perl-Besch (Germany). The capacity of the new UWWTP is 23000 p.e. The generated load with reserve capacity from the cities Remich, Schengen, Remerschen, Wintrange, Wellenstein, Bech-Kleinmacher and Schwebsingen is estimated with 15410 p.e
Row.aggRemarks: for all agglomerations the aggPeriodOver should be 31-12-1998. Actually 18% of the generated load is still treated in decentralized primary treatment facilities. The other 82% are already connected via sewer pipe to the new international UWWTP in the agglomeration of Perl-Besch (Germany). It is foreseen to connect the remaining part of all this sub agglomerations in the future.
